SECURITY AND MAINTENANCE NOTICE
================================

This software is provided free of charge. While we strive to follow security
best practices and modern development standards at the time of release, we
make no guarantee that this code will be maintained, patched, or updated to
address future vulnerabilities.

By using this software, you acknowledge:

1. NO SECURITY GUARANTEE — This code is provided as-is. Security practices
   evolve; what is secure today may not be tomorrow. Review the code yourself
   before deploying in any production or sensitive environment.

2. NO MAINTENANCE COMMITMENT — Issues, pull requests, and vulnerability
   reports are reviewed on a best-effort basis. There is no SLA, support
   contract, or obligation to respond.

3. USE AT YOUR OWN RISK — The authors accept no liability for data loss,
   security breaches, downtime, or any other damages arising from the use
   of this software in any context.

4. BEST EFFORT STANDARDS — We do our best to write clean, secure, and
   well-tested code. Dependencies are pinned where possible. However, we
   cannot guarantee that third-party dependencies remain free of
   vulnerabilities over time.

If you find a security issue, please report it responsibly via the repository's
issue tracker or directly to the maintainer. We appreciate the community's
help in keeping open-source software safe.
